.Dd May 4, 2026
.Dt GOMOD2NIX-GETTING-STARTED 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm gomod2nix-getting-started
.Nd tutorial for converting a Go module project to a Nix-buildable application
.Sh DESCRIPTION
This page walks through the steps required to use
.Sy gomod2nix
to build a Go application reproducibly with Nix.
There are two supported entry points: the
.Sy niv
workflow for projects that pin sources via JSON, and a Nix-Flakes
workflow for projects that already use a
.Pa flake.nix .
.Sh INSTALLATION
.Ss Using niv
First initialize niv and pin gomod2nix:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ niv init --latest
$ niv add nix-community/gomod2nix
.Ed
.Pp
Create a
.Pa shell.nix
to bootstrap the development environment:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{ pkgs ? (
    let
      sources = import ./nix/sources.nix;
    in
    import sources.nixpkgs {
      overlays = [
        (import "${sources.gomod2nix}/overlay.nix")
      ];
    }
  )
}:
let
  goEnv = pkgs.mkGoEnv { pwd = ./.; };
in
pkgs.mkShell {
  packages = [
    goEnv
    pkgs.gomod2nix
    pkgs.niv
  ];
}
.Ed
.Pp
And a
.Pa default.nix
that builds the application:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{ pkgs ? (
    let
      sources = import ./nix/sources.nix;
    in
    import sources.nixpkgs {
      overlays = [
        (import "${sources.gomod2nix}/overlay.nix")
      ];
    }
  )
}:
pkgs.buildGoApplication {
  pname = "myapp";
  version = "0.1";
  pwd = ./.;
  src = ./.;
  modules = ./gomod2nix.toml;
}
.Ed
.Ss Using Nix Flakes
The quickest path is the bundled flake template:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ nix flake init -t github:nix-community/gomod2nix#app
.Ed
.Pp
For container images, use the container template instead:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ nix flake init -t github:nix-community/gomod2nix#container
.Ed
.Sh BASIC USAGE
After entering the development shell, generate
.Pa gomod2nix.toml
from
.Pa go.mod
and
.Pa go.sum :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gomod2nix generate
.Ed
.Pp
To pre-compile dependencies into the build cache for faster subsequent
builds, add
.Fl -with-deps :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gomod2nix generate --with-deps
.Ed
.Pp
.Fl -with-deps
records the imported package set in
.Pa gomod2nix.toml
so the builder can pre-compile them once instead of recompiling on every
build.
This matters most for projects with many dependencies.
.Pp
To skip downloading module sources into the Nix store and reuse the
local Go cache instead:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gomod2nix import
.Ed
.Sh CROSS-PLATFORM LOCKFILES
The
.Sy vendorPackages
list inside
.Pa gomod2nix.toml
is the union of
.Sy go list -deps
results across every target platform the project builds for.
Auto-discovery reads
.Pa flake.nix
via
.Sy nix flake show --json --all-systems
and unions system keys under
.Sy packages.*
and
.Sy legacyPackages.* .
Override the discovered set with
.Fl -target Ar GOOS/GOARCH
.Pq repeatable :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gomod2nix --target linux/amd64 --target darwin/arm64
.Ed
.Pp
Or opt out entirely with
.Fl -no-flake-targets
to fall back to host-only generation.
